  "excerpt": "<p>Use this guide to help you understand how to compare plans and choose one that\u2019s right for you.</p>",
  "content": "<div class=\"ds-l-row\"><div class=\"ds-l-col--12\"><div class=\"ds-u-sm-margin-left--4 ds-u-sm-margin-bottom--4 ds-u-sm-float--right\" style=\"max-width:232px;\"><div class=\"media-modal\" data-modal-heading=\"How to Choose a Plan in the Health Insurance Marketplace\u00ae\"><div class=\"media-modal-trigger\"><article class=\"media media--type-image media--view-mode-default\" data-align=\"center\">\n  \n      \n  <div class=\"field field--name-field-media-image field--type-image field--label-visually_hidden\">\n    <div class=\"field__label visually-hidden\">Image</div>\n              <div class=\"field__item\">    <img loading=\"eager\" data-image-encoded=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" data-image-width=\"220\" data-image-height=\"132\" srcset=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_small_544/public/inline-images/en/how-to-choose-a-plan-in-the-health-insurance-marketplace.jpeg?itok=lUAgaOpf 544w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_medium_768/public/inline-images/en/how-to-choose-a-plan-in-the-health-insurance-marketplace.jpeg?itok=5clPGuod 768w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/en/how-to-choose-a-plan-in-the-health-insurance-marketplace.jpeg?itok=99K5OHo1 1024w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1290px) 1290px, 100vw\" width=\"1024\" height=\"614\" src=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/en/how-to-choose-a-plan-in-the-health-insurance-marketplace.jpeg?itok=99K5OHo1\" alt=\"How to choose a plan in the health insurance marketplace\" title=\"How to choose a plan in the health insurance marketplace\">\n\n\n</div>\n          </div>\n\n            <div class=\"field field--name-field-spanish-image field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__item\"><article class=\"media media--type-image-es media--view-mode-default\">\n  \n      \n            <div class=\"field field--name-field-media-image-spanish field--type-image field--label-hidden field__item\">    <img loading=\"eager\" data-image-encoded=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" data-image-width=\"220\" data-image-height=\"132\" srcset=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_small_544/public/inline-images/es/how-to-choose-a-plan-in-the-health-insurance-marketplace.jpeg?itok=KyAfyvqQ 544w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_medium_768/public/inline-images/es/how-to-choose-a-plan-in-the-health-insurance-marketplace.jpeg?itok=UOgQDlxE 768w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/es/how-to-choose-a-plan-in-the-health-insurance-marketplace.jpeg?itok=fqCXxAPS 1024w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1290px) 1290px, 100vw\" width=\"1024\" height=\"614\" src=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/es/how-to-choose-a-plan-in-the-health-insurance-marketplace.jpeg?itok=fqCXxAPS\" alt>\n\n\n</div>\n      \n  </article>\n</div>\n      \n  </article>\n</div><div class=\"media-modal-content\"><div class=\"yt-iframe\" data-iframe-height=\"400\" data-iframe-src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/E45xOGIcGWo?wmode=transparent&amp;rel=0&amp;enablejsapi=1\" data-iframe-width=\"100%\" title=\"YouTube Embedded Video: The Marketplace for Individuals and Families\">&nbsp;</div></div></div><p>How to Choose a Plan in&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>the Health Insurance&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Marketplace<sup>\u00ae</sup></p></div><p>Choosing a health insurance plan can be complicated. Knowing just a few things before you&nbsp;<a href=\"/see-plans/\">compare plans</a>&nbsp;can make it simpler.</p><ul><li><a href=\"/choose-a-plan/plans-categories\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"c1891a77-1418-4fe1-b8c7-bbc5b59a0821\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-entity-id=\"37846\" data-entity-bundle=\"article\" title=\"Health plan categories: Bronze, Silver, Gold &amp; Platinum\">The 4 \u201cmetal\u201d categories</a>: There are 4 categories of health insurance plans: Bronze, Silver, Gold, and Platinum. These categories show how you and your plan share costs. Plan categories have nothing to do with quality of care.</li><li><a href=\"/choose-a-plan/your-total-costs\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"3ff4c042-5db7-4450-b20b-7170fe56bd90\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-entity-id=\"37861\" data-entity-bundle=\"article\" title=\"Your total costs for health care: Premium, deductible &amp; out-of-pocket costs\">Your total costs for health care</a>: You pay a monthly bill to your insurance company (a \"premium\"), even if you don\u2019t use medical services that month. You pay out-of-pocket costs, including a&nbsp;<a href=\"/glossary/deductible\" title=\"Deductible\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"fcb2fa69-9a31-41eb-a26a-5c76637d7625\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-content=\"The amount you pay for covered health care services before your insurance plan starts to pay. With a $2,000 deductible, for example, you pay the first $2,000 of covered services yourself.\" data-entity-bundle=\"glossary\" data-entity-id=\"34906\" data-internal-href=\"/node/34906\" data-original-title=\"Deductible\">deductible</a>, when you get care. It\u2019s important to think about both kinds of costs when shopping for a plan.</li><li><a href=\"/choose-a-plan/plan-types\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"257e2111-5de5-45a5-9f3a-4d074426245f\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-entity-id=\"37856\" data-entity-bundle=\"article\" title=\"Health insurance plan &amp; network types: HMOs, PPOs, and more\">Plan and network types</a>&nbsp;\u2014&nbsp;<a href=\"/glossary/health-maintenance-organization-hmo\" title=\"Health Maintenance Organization (HMO)\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"5fc39e8d-d443-46f5-9aee-22338d04917b\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-content=\"A type of health insurance plan that usually limits coverage to care from doctors who work for or contract with the HMO. It generally won't cover out-of-network care except in an emergency. An HMO may require you to live or work in its service area to be eligible for coverage. HMOs often provide integrated care and focus on prevention and wellness.\" data-entity-bundle=\"glossary\" data-entity-id=\"35421\" data-internal-href=\"/node/35421\" data-original-title=\"Health Maintenance Organization (HMO)\">HMO</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/glossary/preferred-provider-organization-ppo\" title=\"Preferred Provider Organization (PPO)\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"b4cfe10a-e74f-481e-a6b8-48f66fb5482a\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-content=\"A type of health plan that contracts with medical providers, such as hospitals and doctors, to create a network of participating providers. You pay less if you use providers that belong to the plan\u2019s network. You can use doctors, hospitals, and providers outside of the network for an additional cost.\" data-entity-bundle=\"glossary\" data-entity-id=\"35161\" data-internal-href=\"/node/35161\" data-original-title=\"Preferred Provider Organization (PPO)\">PPO</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"/glossary/point-of-service-plan-pos-plan\" title=\"Point of Service (POS) Plans\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"e84568cd-4c25-4216-96b3-1043162b03a9\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-content=\"A type of plan in which you pay less if you use doctors, hospitals, and other health care providers that belong to the plan\u2019s network. POS plans also require you to get a referral from your primary care doctor in order to see a specialist.\" data-entity-bundle=\"glossary\" data-entity-id=\"35201\" data-internal-href=\"/node/35201\" data-original-title=\"Point of Service (POS) Plans\">POS</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"/glossary/exclusive-provider-organization-epo-plan\" title=\"Exclusive Provider Organization (EPO) Plan\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"21747809-2d6a-4a0f-aeff-b3577d665dcb\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-content=\"A managed care plan where services are covered only if you go to doctors, specialists, or hospitals in the plan\u2019s network (except in an emergency).\" data-entity-bundle=\"glossary\" data-entity-id=\"35506\" data-internal-href=\"/node/35506\" data-original-title=\"Exclusive Provider Organization (EPO) Plan\">EPO</a>: Some plan types allow you to use almost any doctor or health care facility. Others limit your choices or charge you more if you use providers outside their network.</li></ul></div></div><p>Remember that plans also may differ in quality.&nbsp;<a href=\"/quality-ratings\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"eac36223-834f-4962-b829-d8b07983ddd5\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-entity-id=\"35996\" data-entity-bundle=\"article\" title=\"Quality ratings of health plans\">Learn more about quality ratings</a>.</p><div class=\"box-content information-heavyweight\"><p><strong>Want to compare plans &amp; prices now?</strong><br>Provide some income and household information to see plans available in your area, with estimated prices based on your income.</p><p><a class=\"ds-c-button ds-c-button--solid\" href=\"/see-plans/\" data-link-button-type=\"74921\">See plans</a></p></div><h2>More Answers: What to know before you pick a health insurance plan&nbsp;</h2><dl class=\"accordion learn-accordion\"><dt class=\"accordion-title\">How can I learn about the quality of care doctors and hospitals provide?</dt><dd class=\"accordion-content\"><p>You can search, compare, and assess providers, hospitals, and other care facilities using&nbsp;<a href=\"/using-marketplace-coverage/getting-medical-care\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"0e6b6ddf-ea67-490e-8c20-9b3b73722dd4\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-entity-id=\"36851\" data-entity-bundle=\"article\" title=\"Getting regular medical care\">these tools</a>.</p></dd></dl><dl class=\"accordion learn-accordion\"><dt class=\"accordion-title\">How can I find out if I can save on a Marketplace plan?</dt><dd class=\"accordion-content\"><p>Use this quick tool to&nbsp;<a href=\"/lower-costs\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"4bcf3697-3fc1-4cb2-9de4-8735fbf13eae\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-entity-id=\"38081\" data-entity-bundle=\"explainer\" title=\"Saving money on health insurance\">see if your income estimate falls in the range for a premium tax credit and cost-sharing reductions</a>. The type of savings you qualify for may affect which plan category is the best fit for you.</p></dd></dl><dl class=\"accordion learn-accordion\"><dt class=\"accordion-title\">How do I get details on plans I\u2019m interested in, like if my doctors and drugs are covered?</dt><dd class=\"accordion-content\"><p>You can view a summary of benefits, a plan brochure, a provider directory, and a list of covered drugs for each plan. You\u2019ll find links to all of these when you\u2019re comparing Marketplace plans or&nbsp;<a href=\"/see-plans/\">previewing plans and prices</a>&nbsp;before you log in.</p><p>You can also search for your doctors, medical facilities, and prescription drugs when you compare plans. Select your doctors, hospitals and other medical facilities, and prescription drugs. When you view plans, we\u2019ll tell you if each one covers them in network.</p></dd></dl>",
  "url": "/choose-a-plan/comparing-plans"
}